                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d634">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.311F1/176: Telegram (part air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-16T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 16, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 18—7:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>181. At the request of the four principal wheat exporting countries, as expressed
                    in a letter from Ferguson to Secretary General under date of August 3, Avenol
                    telegraphed invitation on August 12 to 27 European countries for conference in
                    London on wheat, commencing August 21st. One reply has been received to date
                    from Greek Government which accepted. If Department desires that the replies of
                    governments be cabled, please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
